Description: Graphics editor for creating  points, and paths.
 The paths consist of segments that can be straight-line
 segments, quadratic or cubic Bezier curves, or splines that
 are implemented as sequences of cubic Bezier curves such that
 the first and second derivatives are continuous functions. The
 paths can be open or closed. Curves can be drawn over an image
 used for reference, with the output values scaled. This editor
 can also measure distances between two points. Several output
 formats are available, one as a set of ECMAScript statements
 that can be used with the org.bzdev.anim2d package and other
 packages based on that package.

